      • create

        protected abstract java.util.Set<DatasetDescriptor> create​(java.io.File file,
                                                           java.io.File workingDir,
                                                           InteractiveServiceProvider.Callback callback)
        Returns the dataset descriptors parsed from the specified file, or null if this spi failed to parse any datasets from the specified file.

        This method should not throw.

        Parameters:
        file - The dataset file
        workingDir - A working directory that will be associated with any descriptors derived from the file and is guaranteed to persist for the lifetime of the descriptor, including through multiple runtimes of the end user application if the descriptor is serialized.
        callback - A callback, may be null
        Returns:
        The parsed descriptors or null if this spi is unable to derive any descriptors for the specified file

        Returns a flag indicating whether or not this spi can derive any datasets from the specified file.
        Parameters:
        file - A dataset file
        callback - A callback, may be null
        Returns:
        true if this spi can derive datasets from the specified file, false otherwise.
